For centuries, families co-slept-snuggled close for warmth, safety, and love. It’s how babies survived, how family bonds were reinforced. Science backs it too: kids learn to regulate their emotions and nervous system through our touch and our closeness, even while they sleep. 

In attachment theory it’s believed that the more close, connected and dependent a child is through early childhood, it actually fosters a deeper sense of independence and security as they grow into themselves. 

Our time with the babies is short… make the mega bed!

Comment “Mega bed” for links to the sheets, duvet and bed frames! Enjoy!!
